data.title: Girl Names: 710 Names You Won’t Find On Other Baby Name Lists
data.meta_description: Find a baby girl name from our list of 710 unique baby girl names you won't find on any other baby names list. As compiled by our community of mums.
data.text:
Searching for the perfect baby girl name? We’ve gathered some of the world’s most beautiful, exotic and unique baby girl names from around the globe.

From the short and sweet to the edgy and out-there, these girl names aren’t for shrinking violets or wallflowers, they’ll help your girl stand out from the crowd, and rock her personality with pride. Many take a modern twist on traditional and popular names.

At the moment, Charlotte tops Australia’s most popular girl’s names, followed by Olivia, Ava and Amelia. All gorgeous names, and there are variations of these beauties in our unique list. The top 100 is rounded off by the super adorable name Olive, a twist on that sublime name comes in at number 481 on our unique list.

So grab a cuppa and take a look at this list that’s brimming with choices that’ll turn heads:

Top 710 unique girl names

Alternative spellings for traditional girl names

It’s time to take another look at the names that have been doing the rounds since our parents were in nappies. There are gems to be found – you’ll never believe how good they look modernised with alternative spellings.

We have a whole article that lists hundreds of Alternative spellings for traditional baby names. Here are a few of our favourties.

We’ve got the scoop on the best baby names for boys or girls. Explore our extensive baby name collections for popular names, unique names, names from around the globe, and top names for boys or girl names.
